22
00:01:49,197 --> 00:01:54,841
Okay, so, um, you guys know me from the committee, but for anyone in the public, my name is Amanda central.

23
00:01:54,981 --> 00:01:58,363
I work in the office of planning, development and sustainability in the city.

24
00:01:59,464 --> 00:02:06,288
And I'm very grateful for the opportunity to present a couple of projects coming out of our office to the committee tonight.

25
00:02:07,129 --> 00:02:09,931
So, first up is the car park pickleball courts.

26
00:02:12,402 --> 00:02:14,123
If I progress the slide here.

27
00:02:15,143 --> 00:02:28,969
So the committee previously granted funding for a planning and redesign process for car park, and many of you likely participated in the outreach and design conversations that happened over the course of 2021.

28
00:02:29,009 --> 00:02:35,152
And so we now have this finalized car park vision plan, which we're very excited about.

29
00:02:35,852 --> 00:02:39,994
And we're working hard to begin to implement, implement that plan.

30
00:02:40,775 --> 00:02:55,943
So, to do so we've broken up the larger vision into several phases, and we'll focus today on phase one, which includes our current CPA proposal, and of course if folks have questions about the other phases happy to answer about that.

31
00:02:57,268 --> 00:03:08,931
So the proposal is for four dedicated pickleball courts, and these would be the first fully dedicated pickleball courts in the city, for which there is strong community need and a lot of desire.

32
00:03:10,032 --> 00:03:18,114
Funding would go towards the design and permitting, bid process, construction, and there's some contingency built into that budget.

33
00:03:19,553 --> 00:03:24,977
The pickleball courts are a discrete portion of phase one of the renovation for Carr Park.

34
00:03:25,938 --> 00:03:48,815
Phase one more broadly includes two baseball fields being reconstructed, the clearing of woodland debris and evasives from kind of the northern woods area of the park, and an accessible loop path and seating and other site furniture, a path connection to Stowers Ave to the park, and drainage and utility work.

35
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:58,916
And bidding out pickleball courts with the other parts of phase one would save the city significant costs on site mobilization.

36
00:03:59,957 --> 00:04:05,623
So let's see if I can forward the slides here.

37
00:04:07,813 --> 00:04:10,996
just to give you guys a sense of what we're talking about here.

38
00:04:11,356 --> 00:04:16,920
So this is the vision plan that emerged out of all of our community conversations.

39
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:27,109
There's a lot of information on here, but I've tried to call out this area here where the pickleball courts would be, which is adjacent to the parking lot and off of the accessible loop path.

40
00:04:29,278 --> 00:04:35,442
We believe that incorporating the courts into this earlier work being done on the park makes sense for a couple of reasons.

41
00:04:36,283 --> 00:04:43,408
The first is that it's an amenity that we think the public would be particularly excited about having access to earlier rather than later.

42
00:04:44,128 --> 00:04:50,693
And I think as we'll hear from some community members tonight, there's a real need for dedicated pickleball courts in the city.

43
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:56,055
Um, otherwise, or in addition to that, um, we talk about staff capacity.

44
00:04:56,115 --> 00:05:02,417
So staff is actually already going to be working on this project and managing other grant work and funding for this phase.

45
00:05:02,517 --> 00:05:07,279
And so it kind of folds in to work that will be already, um, underway.

46
00:05:08,119 --> 00:05:12,761
And we also, uh, want to be cognizant of not disrupting too many parks at the same time.

47
00:05:12,921 --> 00:05:16,322
So focusing this work here, um, we feel makes a lot of sense.

48
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:22,851
And then really quickly, just wanted to give you a rough budget breakdown.

49
00:05:23,512 --> 00:05:33,035
So for the entirety of phase one, including the Pickleball Courts, we've secured grant funding from the Land and Water Conservation Fund for $1 million.

50
00:05:33,855 --> 00:05:37,897
The debt that the city has committed $1.3 million in ARPA funds.

51
00:05:38,517 --> 00:05:46,160
And our ask tonight is for $402,000 from CPA to go towards explicitly the Pickleball Courts.

52
00:05:48,630 --> 00:05:50,611
And I believe that's all that I have.

53
00:05:51,011 --> 00:05:52,992
I'm happy to answer questions at this point.

54
00:05:58,535 --> 00:05:59,456
I have a question.

55
00:06:00,896 --> 00:06:07,140
So we got Tom's letter of support for the pickleball courts.

56
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:16,204
And he specifically mentioned at the end if there was a possibility of making six pickleball courts instead of four.

57
00:06:16,264 --> 00:06:17,025
And I didn't know.

58
00:06:18,299 --> 00:06:23,216
if that was possible, and if so, would that add to the cost that you're requesting?

59
00:06:25,553 --> 00:06:30,675
Yes, so if it were possible, it would add to costs.

60
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:45,779
I think that it would pose some challenges to add additional court space because of where the courts are located in the park and its proximity to the wetlands.

61
00:06:46,179 --> 00:06:50,641
We will be going through a permitting process with the Conservation Commission, as is,

62
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:54,887
because it definitely it falls within the 100 foot buffer zone.

63
00:06:56,990 --> 00:07:01,036
And so I think that there are some constraints on adding additional court space.

64
00:07:01,818 --> 00:07:05,003
Alicia, feel free to hop in if you have any additions.

65
00:07:08,702 --> 00:07:20,249
I think that the one piece that might not be readily obvious when looking at this layout is it might look like, well, there's that big tree, just extend them under the tree.

66
00:07:21,329 --> 00:07:25,392
The tree has root, this is a very big old tree that we're protecting there.

67
00:07:25,412 --> 00:07:31,015
We're actually moving the loop path further into the woods to help protect the roots of this tree.

68
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,256
If you walk out there now,

69
00:07:33,104 --> 00:07:37,047
The path goes very close to the tree and is very disrupted by the roots.

70
00:07:37,808 --> 00:07:48,096
And if you were to dig down as you would need to put a proper base for a pickleball courts under the branches of the tree, it would be very damaging to the roots of the tree.

71
00:07:48,856 --> 00:07:56,102
So we are trying to keep everything out from under the branches of the tree in order to protect the tree itself and its roots.

72
00:07:57,562 --> 00:08:02,824
We can ask our consultant to look at it, but when I eyeball this, I think it'd be very hard.

73
00:08:03,064 --> 00:08:09,467
There's a chance that you could maybe squeeze a fifth one in there, but I'm not sure.

74
00:08:09,487 --> 00:08:15,129
And it would definitely add to the cost because there would be additional materials needed.

75
00:08:16,209 --> 00:08:26,093
So, but how much we'd have to ask, we did only get the letter yesterday, so we haven't actually been able to get a feedback from our designer yet.

76
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:32,901
Yeah, and I and I would add to that there's this consideration of the baseball field space.

77
00:08:33,101 --> 00:08:37,162
So there's a required minimum of 200 feet for the outfield.

78
00:08:37,402 --> 00:08:41,864
It's like home plate to outfield line, which you can kind of see lightly marked off here.

79
00:08:41,884 --> 00:08:47,725
And that's kind of actually the minimum of they offer usually a range for outfield space.

80
00:08:49,066 --> 00:08:56,088
So it I think it's worth asking our consultant, but I could pose some might be a little tricky.

81
00:09:09,673 --> 00:09:11,674
So I don't really have any other questions.

82
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:20,737
I can say that full disclosure, I know Tom, we've played pickleball together at the GMAC gym.

83
00:09:21,417 --> 00:09:29,381
So I know that there is a huge desire to bring permanent pickleball courts to the city of Bedford.

84
00:09:29,461 --> 00:09:34,743
And we've seen lines of people waiting for the pickleball courts.

85
00:09:36,406 --> 00:09:40,549
I don't have any questions beyond the one I already asked.

86
