145
00:15:07,989 --> 00:15:12,272
And I've discussed this with Alicia.

146
00:15:13,353 --> 00:15:15,395
I've lived in Medford for over 30 years.

147
00:15:15,435 --> 00:15:21,259
And I've seen a process going on in our parks, which I think is not a good thing.

148
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:23,041
And that is they are being nibbled

149
00:15:23,788 --> 00:15:32,494
to pieces by the addition of more hard surfaces, more fences, more pavement, et cetera.

150
00:15:32,895 --> 00:15:39,199
And the original purpose of having green space is being vitiated by this syndrome.

151
00:15:39,579 --> 00:15:49,006
Alicia and I talked about the marvelous paving near the tennis courts over at Duggar Park, which has not been fixed, I don't think.

152
00:15:49,026 --> 00:15:52,569
And you look at this picture and it's

153
00:15:53,022 --> 00:15:56,503
another big chunk of paving right in the middle of a public park.

154
00:15:57,443 --> 00:15:58,963
And, you know, when does it stop?

155
00:16:00,083 --> 00:16:04,044
The Mystic River Bend Park, they've added two dog parks.

156
00:16:04,444 --> 00:16:07,425
They've eliminated the meadow effectively.

157
00:16:08,225 --> 00:16:12,366
They added the very large wind turbine smack in the middle of it.

158
00:16:13,046 --> 00:16:16,667
They put a boat ramp, et cetera, on the Mystic River.

159
00:16:18,187 --> 00:16:22,488
The park, I'm sorry, I don't remember the name of it, that's on Webster Street has gradually been

160
00:16:23,317 --> 00:16:27,918
paved over with a lot more paving, et cetera.

161
00:16:28,198 --> 00:16:29,959
I don't think this is what parks are for.

162
00:16:29,999 --> 00:16:35,300
I think they should be green space for people to relax in, to get away from the city.

163
00:16:36,301 --> 00:16:38,781
I don't think they should be full of pavement.

164
00:16:38,861 --> 00:16:41,602
I don't think they should be full of fencing.

165
00:16:41,642 --> 00:16:43,483
