168
00:16:49,344 --> 00:16:51,605
Nobody's actually looked at this

169
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:57,202
Nobody has actually looked at the parks and saying, how are we gonna protect the green space elements here?

170
00:16:57,562 --> 00:17:02,323
Instead, what we have is a stream of projects that do exactly the opposite.

171
00:17:02,343 --> 00:17:07,985
I'm gonna look for some comments from Alicia on this actually.

172
00:17:09,585 --> 00:17:18,008
If I may, this plan is the result of a public process that took place over the last,

173
00:17:19,903 --> 00:17:23,045
18 months that was funded in a prior CPA funding round.

174
00:17:23,866 --> 00:17:40,856
And the uses that have been incorporated into this park are uses that were brought into the plan through a tremendous amount of community input, people who have been looking for these types of uses.

175
00:17:41,176 --> 00:17:42,117
So I'll

176
00:17:43,351 --> 00:17:54,038
I'll allow Alicia to follow up and talk about the planning process by which we arrived at the proposal that we see here this evening for the pickleball courts.

177
00:17:55,098 --> 00:17:57,840
I just want to say, though, that's very well and good.

178
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:03,643
But it doesn't seem to vitiate the trend that is happening here.

179
00:18:03,663 --> 00:18:05,564
And nobody seemed to be concerned about that.

180
00:18:07,085 --> 00:18:11,348
