181
00:18:11,759 --> 00:18:18,706
they want another court, they want another piece of paving, eventually you're not going to have any more green space in Medford Parks.

182
00:18:18,906 --> 00:18:20,228
That's exactly what's going to happen.

183
00:18:27,745 --> 00:18:39,354
So Tom, we may need to agree to disagree on this because I believe that the parks are for the people and that the people want to have active recreation in them and that there are uses that they'd like to see.

184
00:18:40,435 --> 00:18:50,903
This park has a large wetland and woods in it and one of the things we're going to be doing is cleaning some of the debris out of that and restoring that to its natural

185
00:18:51,764 --> 00:18:55,366
area, but people need places to be outside.

186
00:18:55,386 --> 00:19:03,831
They can't walk through meadows, like it sounds like a lovely idea, but everybody's afraid of the ticks.

187
00:19:05,692 --> 00:19:13,237
It's nice to have them, but Medford is a city and we need to be able to have people in our open spaces.

188
00:19:14,085 --> 00:19:21,189
And this is the uses that people would really like to see these are the uses that will bring people out of their houses into our parks.

189
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:24,131
And we really want to support that.

190
00:19:24,991 --> 00:19:25,932
Okay, I'll agree.

191
00:19:26,172 --> 00:19:27,152
