So while the Department of Education, DESE does not currently have guidelines separating preschool playgrounds, early education and care does.

533
00:53:55,492 --> 00:54:01,096
And the industry standard is to separate playgrounds for two to five-year-olds from playgrounds for older children.

534
00:54:01,916 --> 00:54:02,717
So we did that here.

535
00:54:03,157 --> 00:54:05,399
So this would be the elementary playground up here.

536
00:54:05,919 --> 00:54:10,022
And then this area is a developmentally appropriate area for the preschool that is housed there.

537
00:54:11,327 --> 00:54:22,753
Because the McGlynn is the school that houses the program for kids with significant disabilities, including physical disabilities, it was really important that this playground be particularly physically inclusive.

538
00:54:23,914 --> 00:54:28,936
So the structures reflect that and so many of the design choices.

539
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:32,979
So this is a deck, I'll show you pictures of it, but it preserves the existing tree.

