778
01:18:58,729 --> 01:19:10,374
The biggest maintenance concern of this was the drainage and the groundwater, both the groundwater and the surface runoff is a problem here.

779
01:19:10,494 --> 01:19:19,458
So this design actually deals with that with rain gardens as well as sufficient drainage underneath.

780
01:19:19,978 --> 01:19:25,060
So you can see here the flooding marks that the flooding came all the way up at times to the foot of the structure.

781
01:19:25,557 --> 01:19:30,581
And because of the insufficient drainage, it caused the poured-in-place to fail earlier than it would.

782
01:19:31,182 --> 01:19:33,844
Poured-in-place rubber still only lasts 10 to 15 years.

783
01:19:33,984 --> 01:19:39,389
So on any playground, you're going to have to, in general, replace the surfacing before you have to replace the structures.

784
01:19:44,653 --> 01:19:46,615
We don't have to mow any of this.

785
01:19:47,496 --> 01:19:49,958
So there's not so much of that kind of maintenance.

786
01:19:50,657 --> 01:20:00,742
there's only the maintenance that would have to be done anyway of actually inspecting and replacing any parts, which should have been being done the whole time.

787
01:20:04,384 --> 01:20:05,044
I don't know.

788
01:20:07,986 --> 01:20:19,452
We don't have an estimate right now on ongoing maintenance for this particular design, but because so much of it is pavement that we don't have

